The error message you're seeing is related to Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS), which is a security feature implemented by web browsers to prevent requests to different origins (domains, protocols, or ports) from the one the web page came from.

The error message is saying that the server at `https://services.arcgis.com/` is sending the `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header with a value of `*`, which means it allows requests from any origin. However, because your request includes credentials (in this case, the token), the `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header must specify the exact origin that's allowed to make requests, not `*`.

This is a server-side issue, and it can only be fixed by the server administrator. They need to configure the server to send the `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header with the value of your origin (`http://localhost:3000`), or implement a proxy server.

