To download the XML (KML) data as a file, you can create a Blob from the data and then use the `URL.createObjectURL` method to create a URL for the Blob. You can then use this URL to create a link that the user can click to download the file.

Here's how you can do it:

```javascript
// Convert the KML object to XML
let xml = parse('kml', kml, {format: true});

// Create a Blob from the XML data
let blob = new Blob([xml], {type: 'application/vnd.google-earth.kml+xml'});

// Create a URL for the Blob
let url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);

// Create a link for the URL and trigger a click event to start the download
let link = document.createElement('a');
link.href = url;
link.download = 'data.kml'; // specify the file name
link.click();
```

