In KML, styles are defined at the Document or Folder level and are identified by a unique ID. They can be applied to individual Placemarks within the Document or Folder by referencing the style's ID.

Here's how you can add a style to your folders:

```javascript
let kml = {
  Document: Object.keys(folders).map(status => {
    let folder = {
      Folder: {
        name: status,
        Style: { // Add this block to define a style
          id: 'style-' + status,
          LineStyle: {
            color: 'ff0000ff', // Red color
            width: 5
          },
          PolyStyle: {
            color: '50F0F0F0' // Semi-transparent gray color
          }
        },
        Placemark: folders[status].map(feature => {
          let kmlFeature = tokml(feature);
          kmlFeature.styleUrl = '#style-' + status; // Apply the style to the Placemark
          return kmlFeature;
        })
      }
    };
    return folder;
  })
};
```

