The `sendMail` function from `nodemailer` returns a `Promise` that resolves with an `info` object when the email is successfully sent. This `info` object contains information about the sent message, including the `messageId`, `envelope`, `accepted`, `rejected`, `pending`, and `response`.

If you want to return the email that was sent, you can return the `info` object from your `sendEmail` function. Here's how you can do it:

```javascript
async function sendEmail(email, body, subject) {
  const transporter = nodemailer.createTransport({
    host: process.env.SMPT,
    port: process.env.SMPT_PORT,
    secure: false, // true for SSL, false for TLS
    auth: {
      user: process.env.SMTP_EMAIL,
      pass: process.env.SMTP_SENHA
    }
  });

  // Email configuration
  const mailOptions = {
    from: process.env.SMTP_EMAIL,
    to: email,
    subject: subject,
    text: body
  };

  // Send the email
  const info = await transporter.sendMail(mailOptions);
  transporter.close();

  return info;
}
```

Now, when you call `sendEmail`, it will return a `Promise` that resolves with the `info` object. You can use this `info` object to get information about the sent email.

