This error might be caused by an incorrect configuration of the Dojo loader or a missing module in your project's dependencies. However, it's also possible that this error is caused by a conflict between Dojo and Webpack, which you seem to be using to bundle your application.

Webpack doesn't understand Dojo's module syntax out of the box. To make them work together, you might need to use a plugin or loader that can handle Dojo's modules, such as `dojo-webpack-plugin`.

Here's an example of how you can configure `dojo-webpack-plugin` in your `webpack.config.js`:

```javascript
const DojoWebpackPlugin = require('dojo-webpack-plugin');

module.exports = {
  // ...
  plugins: [
    new DojoWebpackPlugin({
      loaderConfig: {
        // Configuration options for Dojo loader
        paths: {
          // Map paths for Dojo modules
        },
        has: {
          // Feature flags for Dojo
          'host-browser': true,  // This might fix your issue
        },
      },
      environment: {dojoRoot: 'node_modules'},  // Where to look for Dojo
      locales: ['en-us'],  // Supported locales
    }),
    // ...
  ],
  // ...
};
```

