response.value:
The CSS styling rules cannot be added directly in the JavaScript file. They need to be added in a CSS file. However, you can inject CSS rules into your page using JavaScript. Here's how you can do it:

```javascript
const editor = new Editor({
    view: view,
    layerInfos: layerInfos,
    attributeUpdatesEnabled: false,
    addEnabled: false,
    deleteEnabled: false,
    visibleElements : {
      undoRedoButtons:true,
    }
});

editor.container.classList.add("custom-editor");

// Inject CSS rules
const style = document.createElement('style');
style.innerHTML = `
  .custom-editor .esri-editor__undo-redo-buttons {
    display: block;
  }
`;
document.head.appendChild(style);

console.log("elementos do editor")
console.log(editor)

const EditorExpand = new Expand({
  view: view,
  content: editor,
  icon: "edit-geometry"   
});

view.ui.add(EditorExpand, "top-right");
```

This code creates a new `<style>` element, sets its `innerHTML` to the CSS rules you want to add, and then appends it to the `<head>` of the document. This effectively adds the CSS rules to the page.

